WHEREAS, the Center for Literacy & Learning employs a comprehensive literacy
wraparound approach, which provides services to educators, families, and communities that
support learning both inside and outside the classroom; and
WHEREAS, in 2019, the Center for Literacy & Learning successfully advocated for
the creation of the Early Literacy Commission; in 2024, it successfully pushed for the
establishment of the Louisiana Literacy Advisory Commission; both commissions are
instrumental in shaping literacy policies in the state; and
WHEREAS, the Center for Literacy & Learning, in partnership with the state
Department of Education, launched the Literacy Coaching Program in 2020; and
WHEREAS, in 2023, the Center for Literacy & Learning launched the Louisiana
Pilot Program for family engagement in literacy education; and
WHEREAS, improving literacy across Louisiana is vital to building a strong
workforce, creating high-quality jobs, and sustaining long-term economic growth.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Tuesday, May 5, 2026, as Literacy Day at
the state capitol; does hereby commend the work of the Center for Literacy & Learning; and
does hereby celebrate the notable progress in fourth grade literacy scores in Louisiana.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
